.TH dkp-registry-pack 1  "pack 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
dkp\-registry\-pack \- Pack\-level management subcommands
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdkp registry pack\fR [\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-\-audience\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Pack\-level management subcommands
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR [default: plain]
Output format
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
plain: Human\-readable plain text (default)
.IP \(bu 2
table: Aligned table using comfy\-table
.IP \(bu 2
json: Pretty\-printed JSON
.RE
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress informational output; print only results
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Print debug info (schema paths, provider calls, etc.)
.TP
\fB\-\-audience\fR \fI<ID>\fR
Filter content to assets tagged for a specific audience profile
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
dkp\-registry\-pack\-versions(1)
List all published versions of a pack
.TP
dkp\-registry\-pack\-set\-visibility(1)
Set pack visibility
.TP
dkp\-registry\-pack\-grant(1)
Grant access to a private pack
.TP
dkp\-registry\-pack\-revoke(1)
Revoke access to a private pack
.TP
dkp\-registry\-pack\-access(1)
List accounts with access to a private pack
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
